dataset.title: Akaroa, Tide Predictions, 2017
dataset.description: Akaroa, Tide Predictions, 2017. Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. dataset.title: Auckland, Sea Level Data 2009
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

dataset.title: Gisborne, Tide Predictions, 2017
dataset.description: Gisborne, Tide Predictions, 2017. Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats

dataset.title: Kaikoura, Sea Level Data 2010
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats

dataset.title: Korotiti Bay, Great Barrier Island, Sea Level Data 2010
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

dataset.title: Owenga, Chatham Islands, Sea Level Data 2007
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats

dataset.title: Puysegur, Sea Level Data 2009
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format, and display the daily times and levels of high and low tides, for a particular location.Use the PDF files if you want to print the tide tables, and the CSV files if you wish to import the data into another programme. dataset.title: Tory Channel / Kura te Au Tidal Stream Predictions 2019
dataset.description: Tory Channel / Kura te Au tidal stream predictions.Tables are provided in both PDF and comma delimited text (CSV) format. A tidal stream is the periodic movement of water in a horizontal direction that is due ultimately to the same astronomical causes as the tide (whereas the tide is a movement in the vertical direction).The tidal stream predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.

dataset.title: Wellington, Sea Level Data 2007
dataset.description: Sea level data recorded at the monitoring sites is available for download. The primary purpose of the network is to upgrade and improve New Zealand's response to tsunami hazards. However, the data generated can also be used for other purposes.The zipped data file contain data for each day, with readings at one minute intervals.

dataset.title: Wellington, Tide Predictions, 2017
dataset.description: Wellington, Tide Predictions, 2017. The tide predictions on this website are not official tide tables as specified in Maritime Rules Part 25 Nautical Charts and Publications (pursuant to Section 36 of the Maritime Transport Act 1994).LINZ accepts no liability for any direct, indirect, consequential or incidental damages that result from any errors in the information, whether due to LINZ or a third party, or that arise from the use, or misuse, of the information available from this site.For more information see https://www.linz.govt.nz/sea/tides/tide-predictions/tide-prediction-formats
